Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of minimising discrete energies defined over factors, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a technique to automatically select the best inference algorithm for an input GM, which involves machine learning and decision-making, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves experimentation and validation, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
